Carousel

Basic carousel

Carousels can use just about any content for each slide, and the number of slides you can use is also flexible. The control sizing and position has been designed with the jumbotron in mind, so for simplest implementation, use a jumbotron for each slide layout.

    • Jumbotron

    Basic Jumbotron

    The Jumbotron (AKA Billboard) is used to showcase important information in a prominent position on the page.

    Important Headline

    Create interactive, decision logic based experiences for your customers! A Journey can house anything from a simple email to a complex year-long multi-stage campaign that reacts to the actions taken by the recipients along the way.

    Action

    Without side padding

    If you don't want the side padding on a jumbotron, just add the jumbotron-fluid class. You can then add an element with .container or .container-fluid inside the jumbotron to align the content to the grid.

    This variation is handy if you want to apply a full-bleed background to the jumbotron itself.

    No side padding

    Ok, well there is side padding, but not on the Jumbotron itself. The side padding here comes from the .container-fluid inside the jumbotron.

    Got it

    Dark background

    Add the bg-dark class directly to the jumbotron as shown below, or place inside another container with bg-dark applied.

    Important Headline

    Create interactive, decision logic based experiences for your customers! A Journey can house anything from a simple email to a complex year-long multi-stage campaign that reacts to the actions taken by the recipients along the way.

    Action

    Background image

    Use custom CSS to apply a background image to the jumbotron. The example below uses inline styles for demonstration purposes, but these custom styles should be in your application-specific stylesheet.

    If your background image is dark, you can include the bg-dark class to make the text readable.

    Light background image

    This example uses a background image with a semi-transparent white linear gradient to add a light color mask to the background image and ensure readability.

    Sweet

    Dark background image

    Adding the bg-dark class takes care of inverting the text, and then the same linear gradient trick is used to add a dark color overlay to ensure that the white text stands out.

    Nice

    Modal

    Basic example

    Use modals to display information to the user in a dialog-style overlay. Just about anything can be put into a modal, and they automatically scroll if the content is longer than the viewport.

    Off-canvas

    Off-canvas panel

    Off-canvas panels can be used for navigation lists, filters, and more. Panels can be positioned on the left or right side of the page.

    The example below shows a panel triggered by a button in the navbar, but they can be toggled by a button anywhere using data-toggle="off-canvas" and the corresponding data-target="#..."

    Panel title

    • Group title 1
      • KPIs
      • Social stream
      • History
    • Group title 2

      • Settings
